@startuml

title Private Vocabulary Flashcard Entity Schema

entity "VocabularyEntity\n(vocabulary_entries)" as VocabularyEntity {
  * id : String
  --
  * user_id : String
  * surface : String
  * translation : String
  * entry_kind : String
  notes : String
  * schema_version : Integer
  * created_at : Instant
  * updated_at : Instant
}

entity "VocabularyExampleSentenceEntity\n(vocabulary_example_sentences)" as VocabularyExampleSentenceEntity {
  * id : String
  --
  * entry_id : String
  * sentence : String
  * translation : String
  * display_order : Integer
}

entity "FlashCardReviewEntity\n(flashcard_review)" as FlashCardReviewEntity {
  * id : String
  --
  * user_id : String
  * language_content_id : String
  * content_type : String
  * is_reversed : Boolean
  * card_json : jsonb
}

VocabularyEntity ||--|{ VocabularyExampleSentenceEntity : exampleSentences
VocabularyEntity ||..o{ FlashCardReviewEntity : language_content_id logical reference

note right of FlashCardReviewEntity
Constraints:
- unique(language_content_id, content_type, user_id, is_reversed)
- content_type in ('VOCABULARY', 'SENTENCE', 'CHUNK')

Rule:
- For private vocabulary generation:
  exactly two rows per vocabulary per user
  one is_reversed=false and one is_reversed=true.
  Vocabulary flashcard domain reads/writes only rows where content_type='VOCABULARY'.
end note

note right of FlashCardReviewEntity
Contains FSRS scheduling state only.
No card front/back text is stored.
end note

note bottom of VocabularyEntity
All flashcard content is resolved from:
- vocabulary_entries.surface / translation
- vocabulary_example_sentences.sentence / translation
end note

note left of FlashCardReviewEntity
Module boundaries:
- `flashcards_study/infrastructure/jpa/*` owns flashcard persistence.
- `language_learning_system/infra/jpa/vocabulary/*` owns vocabulary persistence.
- Cross-capability coupling stays at ID reference level only.
- Boundary mapping should be explicit in mapper classes (MapStruct).
end note

note bottom of FlashCardReviewEntity
`FlashCardReview` is the shared domain shape for vocabulary, sentence, and chunk references.
Vocabulary response payloads are assembled through domain model `VocabularyFlashCardData`
before mapping to API view DTOs.
end note

@enduml
